The paper discusses a practical approach for answering why and why-not provenance questions for queries with negation, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB) and logic (cs.LO). The approach involves rewriting Datalog rules and using SQL to compute explanations, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions optimizations to prune parts of a provenance graph, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
